statement.p:
Let A_1, A_2, \ldots, A_k form a partition of S.
Show that the relation R = \{(x,y) : x \text{ and } y \text{ are in the same $A_i$}\}
is an equivalence relation on S.

			Solve the following congruences.
			Express your answer as congruence classes of the original modulus.


4x \equiv 8 \Mod{5}

4x \equiv 3 \Mod{5}

2x \equiv 10 \Mod{8}

33x + 4 \equiv 2 \Mod{7}

100x - 23 \equiv 11 \Mod{99}

31 - 11x \equiv 4x + 8 \Mod{44}

			Compute each quantity:


2^{2020} \mmod{5}

2^{2020} \mmod{7}

2^{2020} \mmod{11}

2^{2020} \mmod{385}
